NAME
    Task::Newbie - Make life easy for newbies

VERSION
    Version 0.001

SYNOPSIS
     wget -O- http://xrl.us/cpanm | perl - Task::Newbie

WHAT THIS MODULE DOES
    At the minute, not a lot, but here's what it will do:

    configure more sane defaults for CPAN.pm and CPANPLUS.pm
    install the basic modules that a newbie is likely to want/need

AUTHOR
    James Laver, "<cpan at jameslaver.com>"

BUGS
    Please report any bugs or feature requests to "bug-task-newbie at
    rt.cpan.org", or through the web interface at
    <http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/ReportBug.html?Queue=Task-Newbie>. I will be
    notified, and then you'll automatically be notified of progress on your
    bug as I make changes.

SUPPORT
    You can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

        perldoc Task::Newbie

    You can also look for information at:

    *   RT: CPAN's request tracker

        <http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Task-Newbie>

    *   AnnoCPAN: Annotated CPAN documentation

        <http://annocpan.org/dist/Task-Newbie>

    *   CPAN Ratings

        <http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Task-Newbie>

    *   Search CPAN

        <http://search.cpan.org/dist/Task-Newbie/>

